# Output Generation Skill

Standard patterns for generating Sigma Protocol artifacts with consistent structure.

## PRD Template

```markdown
# PRD: [Feature ID] - [Feature Name]

**Version:** 1.0.0
**Status:** Draft | In Review | Approved | Implemented

## Overview

### User Story
As a [user type], I want to [action] so that [benefit].

### Success Metrics
| Metric | Target | Measurement |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| [KPI] | [Target] | [How measured] |

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] AC1: [Testable criterion]
- [ ] AC2: [Testable criterion]

## BDD Scenarios

```gherkin
Given [precondition]
When [action]
Then [expected result]
```

## Edge Cases

| Case | Expected Behavior |
|------|-------------------|
| [Case] | [Behavior] |

## Out of Scope
- [Explicitly excluded feature]
```

## Directory Structure

```
docs/
├── specs/MASTER_PRD.md
├── architecture/ARCHITECTURE.md
├── ux/UX-DESIGN.md
├── flows/FLOW-TREE.md
├── design/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md
├── prds/
│   ├── PRD-INDEX.md
│   └── F01-feature-name.md
└── analysis/
```

## File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| PRD | `F[##]-[kebab-case].md` | `F01-user-auth.md` |
| Analysis | `[TYPE]-YYYY-MM-DD.md` | `GAP-ANALYSIS-2026-01-04.md` |

## Quality Checklist

- [ ] No ambiguous language (should, maybe, TBD)
- [ ] All placeholders replaced
- [ ] Version and date current
- [ ] Code snippets syntactically correct
- [ ] BDD scenarios follow Gherkin syntax
- [ ] Acceptance criteria testable
- [ ] Dependencies documented

## HITL Checkpoint Format

```markdown
## HITL Checkpoint: [Name]

**What's Complete:**
- [Item]

**What Needs Review:**
1. [Question or decision needed]

**Your Options:**
- Approve: Type "approved"
- Revise: Provide feedback
- Reject: Explain concerns
```
